</div><footer class="entry-footer"></footer><div class='post_delimiter'></div></div><div class='post_author_timeline'></div></article><article class='post-entry post-entry-type-standard post-entry-6696 post-loop-2 post-parity-even post-entry-last single-small with-slider post-6696 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-labs-zh-hans tag-dwc-zh-hans tag-implied-volatility-zh-hans tag-labs-zh-hans tag-mean-reversion-zh-hans tag-real-time-sentiment-zh-hans tag-sentiment-index-zh-hans tag-vix-zh-hans tag-volatility-zh-hans tag-volatility-index-zh-hans' itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="https://schema.org/BlogPosting"><div class='blog-meta'><a href='https://blog.darwinex.com/dwc-real-time-trader-sentiment-security/?lang=zh-hans' class='small-preview' title='$DWC &#8211; A Real Time Sentiment Index &#038; Security'><img width="180" height="90" src="https://blog.darwinex.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/trader-sentiment-feature-image-1.jpg" class="attachment-square size-square wp-post-image" alt="Real-Time Trader Sentiment" srcset="https://blog.darwinex.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/trader-sentiment-feature-image-1.jpg 2000w, https://blog.darwinex.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/trader-sentiment-feature-image-1-300x150.jpg 300w, https://blog.darwinex.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/trader-sentiment-feature-image-1-768x384.jpg 768w, https://blog.darwinex.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/trader-sentiment-feature-image-1-1030x515.jpg 1030w" sizes="(max-width: 180px) 100vw, 180px" /><span class="iconfont" aria-hidden='true' data-av_icon='' data-av_iconfont='entypo-fontello'></span></a></div><div class='entry-content-wrapper clearfix standard-content'><header class="entry-content-header"><h2 class='post-title entry-title' itemprop="headline"> <a href='https://blog.darwinex.com/dwc-real-time-trader-sentiment-security/?lang=zh-hans' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: $DWC &#8211; A Real Time Sentiment Index &#038; Security'>$DWC &#8211; A Real Time Sentiment Index &#038; Security <span class='post-format-icon minor-meta'></span> </a></h2><span class='post-meta-infos'><time class='date-container minor-meta updated' itemprop="datePublished" datetime="2017-07-05T19:08:54+00:00">5 July 2017</time><span class='text-sep text-sep-date'>/</span><span class='comment-container minor-meta'><a href="https://blog.darwinex.com/dwc-real-time-trader-sentiment-security/?lang=zh-hans#respond" class="comments-link">0 Comments</a></span><span class='text-sep text-sep-comment'>/</span><span class="blog-categories minor-meta">in <a href="https://blog.darwinex.com/category/labs-zh-hans/?lang=zh-hans" rel="tag">实验室</a> </span><span class="text-sep text-sep-cat">/</span><span class="blog-author minor-meta">by <span class="entry-author-link" itemprop="name"><span class="vcard author"><span class="fn"><a href="https://blog.darwinex.com/author/the-market-bull/?lang=zh-hans" title="Posts by The Market Bull" rel="author">The Market Bull</a></span></span></span></span></span></header><div class="entry-content" itemprop="text"><div id="attachment_6484" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignright"><img class="wp-image-6484 size-medium" src="https://blog.darwinex.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/DWC-With-Boundaries-300x193.png" alt="DWC - Normalized (With Range Boundaries)" width="300" height="193" srcset="https://blog.darwinex.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/DWC-With-Boundaries-300x193.png 300w, https://blog.darwinex.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/DWC-With-Boundaries.png 700w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /><p class="wp-caption-text">DWC &#8211; Normalized (With Range Boundaries)</p></div>
<p>Fundamental and Technical trading indicators have long been used as a proxy for <strong>market sentiment</strong>.</p>
<p>But by definition, these indicators have always <strong>lagged</strong> the movements they&#8217;ve been used to forecast.</p>
<p>With the advent of &#8220;Big Data&#8221;, social data too has joined the ranks, e.g. Twitter, Facebook, LinkedIn, with various attempts being made to harness any potentially predictive patterns through &#8220;<strong>opinion mining</strong>&#8220;.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2></h2>
<h2>However, <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Real-Time</span> Sentiment Analysis continues to be an elusive, ever-evolving challenge.</h2>
<p><strong>The Challenge:</strong> Measuring in real-time, how market participants are presently orientated.</p>
<p><strong>The Solution:</strong> DARWIN <strong>DWC</strong>? ..continue reading for the answer.</p>
<p><em>If you missed our first post introducing DARWIN $DWC, <a href="https://blog.darwinex.com/dwc-hedging-darwin/?lang=zh-hans&amp;utm_campaign=darwinex-labs&amp;utm_source=main-blog&amp;utm_medium=post&amp;utm_content=dwc-vs-vix" target="_blank" rel="noopener">you may read it here.</a></em></p>
<hr />
<h2>DWC &#8211; An Index &amp; Tradable Security bundled into one.</h2>
<p><a href="https://www.darwinex.com/darwin/DWC.4.20/?utm_source=main-blog&amp;utm_medium=post&amp;utm_content=dwc-vix-sentiment" target="_blank" rel="noopener">DWC</a> is Darwinex Labs&#8217; first attempt at openly addressing the problem of lagged sentiment.</p>
<p>By leveraging community exposure in a manner that protects individual trader IP, DWC shows how the Darwinex trader collective is inclined in real-time.</p>
<p>As a <strong>Real-Time</strong> Sentiment Indicator, DWC also exhibits the following features:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>24/5 LIQUIDITY</strong> during market hours.
<div id="attachment_6477" style="width: 1153px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img class="wp-image-6477 size-full" src="https://blog.darwinex.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/DWC-Trading-Journal.png" alt="DWC - Instantly Liquid During Market Hours" width="1143" height="753" srcset="https://blog.darwinex.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/DWC-Trading-Journal.png 1143w, https://blog.darwinex.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/DWC-Trading-Journal-300x198.png 300w, https://blog.darwinex.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/DWC-Trading-Journal-768x506.png 768w, https://blog.darwinex.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/DWC-Trading-Journal-1030x679.png 1030w" sizes="(max-width: 1143px) 100vw, 1143px" /><p class="wp-caption-text">DWC &#8211; Instantly Liquid During Market Hours</p></div>
<p>&nbsp;</li>
<li><strong>Tradable 24/5</strong> -&gt; the ability to buy into sentiment directly (i.e. buy DWC) eliminates the need for considering purchases of index-linked Exchange Traded Funds (ETFs) or Notes (ETNs) as is the case with say the VIX Implied Volatility Index.
<div id="attachment_6447" style="width: 1155px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img class="wp-image-6447 size-full" src="https://blog.darwinex.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/DWC-Darwin-Header.png" alt="DWC - Real Time Community Sentiment" width="1145" height="184" srcset="https://blog.darwinex.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/DWC-Darwin-Header.png 1145w, https://blog.darwinex.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/DWC-Darwin-Header-300x48.png 300w, https://blog.darwinex.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/DWC-Darwin-Header-768x123.png 768w, https://blog.darwinex.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/DWC-Darwin-Header-1030x166.png 1030w" sizes="(max-width: 1145px) 100vw, 1145px" /><p class="wp-caption-text">DWC &#8211; Real Time Community Sentiment</p></div>
<p>&nbsp;</li>
<li><strong>Cyclical / Mean Reverting</strong> -&gt; trading a reasonably predictable, well-defined, mean-reverting price range is high on every trader/investor&#8217;s wishlist.
<div id="attachment_6478" style="width: 627px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img class="wp-image-6478 size-full" src="https://blog.darwinex.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/DWC-Quotes-Original.png" alt="DWC - Price Quotes" width="617" height="540" srcset="https://blog.darwinex.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/DWC-Quotes-Original.png 617w, https://blog.darwinex.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/DWC-Quotes-Original-300x263.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 617px) 100vw, 617px" /><p class="wp-caption-text">DWC &#8211; Price Quotes</p></div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div id="attachment_6484" style="width: 710px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img class="wp-image-6484 size-full" src="https://blog.darwinex.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/DWC-With-Boundaries.png" alt="DWC - Normalized (With Range Boundaries)" width="700" height="450" srcset="https://blog.darwinex.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/DWC-With-Boundaries.png 700w, https://blog.darwinex.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/DWC-With-Boundaries-300x193.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /><p class="wp-caption-text">DWC &#8211; Normalized (With Range Boundaries)</p></div>
<p>&nbsp;</li>
<li><strong>HIGH CAPACITY</strong> &#8211; With a current maximum investment capacity of <strong>1.2 to 1.5 Billion USD</strong>, there is plenty of retail volume this asset can take to market with little to no market impact -&gt; community IP remains protected at all times, trader/investor interests remain aligned, no conflict of interest.</li>
<li><strong>DWC replicates the opposite of the trader collective&#8217;s behaviour &#8211; </strong>A significant majority of traders routinely demonstrate Loss Aversion (keep losing trades open in confidence that odds are favourable, but close winning trades too soon). The pitfalls of loss aversion make themselves particularly well known during deep market movements. For more details on this, <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://blog.darwinex.com/dwc-hedging-darwin/?lang=zh-hans&amp;utm_campaign=darwinex-labs&amp;utm_source=main-blog&amp;utm_medium=post&amp;utm_content=dwc-vs-vix" target="_blank" rel="noopener">please refer to our first post on DWC.</a></span></li>
<li>As DWC replicates the opposite of trader behaviour,<strong> it rises during such times.</strong></li>
</ol>
<h3></h3>
<h3>DWC can therefore be used by Darwinex traders and investors as:</h3>
<p>1) A &#8220;hedge&#8221; during turbulent, deep market movements.</p>
<p>2) A reasonably stable, range-bound asset to trade on its own otherwise.</p>
<h2></h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2>Conclusions:</h2>
<ol>
<li>This post highlighted that the DWC moves <strong>with trader sentiment in real-time</strong>, realizing progress in <strong>&#8220;human cognition&#8221; led asset management.</strong></li>
<li>Traders stand to benefit from the <strong>mean-reverting</strong> nature of the DWC offering range-trading and hedging opportunities.</li>
<li>DWC is <strong>a sentiment indicator and directly tradable asset.</strong></li>
</ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2>What happens next?</h2>
<p>In future posts, we will commence publishing several streams of quantitative research (e.g. ARIMA/GARCH modeling, deep learning experiments, etc) that we&#8217;ve been conducting on the DWC dataset.</p>
<p>Stay tuned!</p>
